  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NDEBUMOG- Finance for Development</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Niger Delta Budget Monitoring Group (NDEBUMOG) has been Novib&apos;s partner since 2013 working on budget transparency and accountability, recall that public finance accountability and transparency has been central to Oxfam#s governance engagement in Nigeria.

Forthe Nigeria F4D SP project implementation, the Actor will carry out applied budget work in the pro-poor sectors of Agricultural, Education and Health using the approach of comparative analysis to determine percentage allocations, investment inthe sector, etc.  This approach will help make available reliable data to be used by the CSOs for advocacy engagement. It will also help consolidate theexisting CSOs# platforms for applied budget work round the Budget cycle, Procurement Monitoring and Budget Tracking and Evaluation to give cohesion and increase impact of activities.

To reach the grassroots communities with relevant fiscal information concerningtheir constituencies, they will be provided with basic economic literacy through Town Hallmeetings across selected LGAs.

At the national level, the planned activities are lobby, advocacy, legislative engagement, campaigns, etc. to spur the Federal government into action to strengthen participatory budgetary process and implementation in Nigeria. In addition, there will be activities like capacity building for CSOs on participatory budgeting, gender based budgeting, etc</narrative>
  </description>
