   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Niger Delta Budget Monitoring Group (NDEBUMOG)</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Niger Delta Budget Monitoring Group, NDEBUMOG is a regional non- governmental organization formed in 2005, and works in the areas of budget advocacy, transparency, accountability and anti-corruption in the Niger Delta and Nigeria in general. It has the mission to promote transparency and accountability in the public resource management through pro-poor budgeting and anti-corruption in theNiger Delta and democratic consolidation in Nigeria. Novib and NDEBUMOG started collaborating in 2011 to support small initiative of Deepening Expenditure Line Tracking of States and LGAs within the Niger Delta focusing on mobilizing citizens and building capacity for the expenditure tracking using participatory approaches.

Following the success of the DELT4SLOG1, as reported in the 2012 Narrative report and observed by the toolbox team in March 2013, Oxfam Novib decided to support the planned DELT4SLOG 2 to deepen the achieved outcomes of the project in 2012.   The project aims to gather useful budget data for advocacy through desk review and field budget tracking of capital projects in the selected locations, strengthen the capacity of CSOs, NDEBUMOG staff, Journalists and community representatives on budget tracking, and established platforms of engagement in Rivers, Bayelsa and Delta States to hold governments accountable on its stewardship through dialogue with the Legislatures and other government representatives.</narrative>
  </participating-org>
